      <Description>Level 1D files contain a thumbnail image (PNG) for a stack of 8 slices for different latitudes of 
   brightness as a function of wavelength and tangent altitude. A new L1D file is generated for each new L1C file. 
   These correspond to either the Northern or Southern hemisphere. Stack of 8 slices for different latitudes of 
   intensity as a function of wavelength and altitude:
   -Use the 8 latitudes that correspond to the scan hemisphere (since there are 16 latitudes per hemisphere, 
   2 latitude bins are co-added to get to 8 latitudes). 
   -Latitudes are +/- [0.625, 1.875, 3.125, 4.375, 5.625, 6.875, 8.125, 9.375]</Description>
